nl.tno.stormcv.model

Class Feature

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tno.stormcv.model.CVParticle
      • nl.tno.stormcv.model.Feature
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<CVParticle>

    public class Feature
extends CVParticle
    This CVParticle implementation represents a single feature calculated for Frame and has the following fields:
    • name: the name of the feature like 'SIFT', 'SURF', 'HOG' etc
    • duration: the duration of the feature in case it describes a temporal aspect of multiple frames
    • sparseDescriptors: a list with Descriptor objects used to described sparse features like SIFT
    • denseDescriptors: a three dimensional float array much like the OpenCV Mat object which can be used to represent dense features like dense Optical Flow
    It is not always clear how a specific descriptor should be stored and it is typically up to the characteristics of the topology and context what is the best way to go.
    Author:
    Corne Versloot
